  "knowledge": [
    {
      "content": "Aristotle's doctrine: heavier objects fall proportionally faster.",
      "content_hash": "ded976fbb1a5df7d567d62da592968afb5d1bea076f9dc50b93923e38cb0dc08",
      "id": "galileo:galileo_falling_bodies::aristotle_doctrine",
      "is_input": false,
      "label": "aristotle_doctrine",
      "metadata": {},
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "setting"
    },
    {
      "content": "Observations show heavier stones fall faster than feathers.",
      "content_hash": "00413432cf9f814d71e1d670b55390133c594d945017143119659daae7fd448f",
      "id": "galileo:galileo_falling_bodies::heavy_falls_faster",
      "is_input": true,
      "label": "heavy_falls_faster",
      "metadata": {},
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The tied composite should be slower (light ball drags heavy ball).\n        $v_{\\text{composite}} = \\frac{m_1 v_1 + m_2 v_2}{m_1 + m_2}$",
      "content_hash": "cffc0c7cf851740f913c022e89b4df0c2cc80ca46d45cd630e1930712776e8e7",
      "id": "galileo:galileo_falling_bodies::composite_slower",
      "is_input": true,
      "label": "composite_slower",
      "metadata": {},
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The composite has greater mass, so it should be faster.\n        $v_{\\text{composite}} = k(m_1 + m_2) > k m_1$",
      "content_hash": "c1b3c8b0c6c796d2cd8e7f824ce95441047a37bccfedc8b8d79285a3c2e9bc5c",
      "id": "galileo:galileo_falling_bodies::composite_faster",
      "is_input": true,
      "label": "composite_faster",
      "metadata": {},
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "not_both_true(A, B)",
      "content_hash": "468923920550aff97ac2349f7d0a5b32e6560066b45861bf367db7f40e8649a7",
      "id": "galileo:galileo_falling_bodies::tied_ball",
