    {
      "content": "Observed speed differences are caused entirely by air resistance.",
      "content_hash": "f63d90631cce18d9d452f535fa8d29d3056189cc5493ecbd77abcd85e0d7a52a",
      "id": "galileo:galileo_falling_bodies::air_resistance",
      "is_input": false,
      "label": "air_resistance",
      "metadata": {},
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "In a vacuum, objects of different mass fall at the same rate.\n        $g \\approx 9.8 \\text{ m/s}^2$, independent of mass.",
